  "title": "Search not firing on externally trigerred input event",
  "body": "I need to have a field that, when typed in, shows the main search field and starts searching.\n\nThis is what I have: \n\n``` javascript\n    $('.search-trigger').on('input', function() {\n        const $this = $(this);\n        const val = $this.val();\n\n        if (val) {\n            const $searchInput = $('#algolia-mobile-search-input').find('input');\n            $searchInput.val(val);\n            $searchInput.focus();\n            $searchInput.trigger('input');\n        }\n    });\n```\n\nThe value is set on the main input, but the search isn't performed. Maybe I'm approaching this from a wrong angle, but I expected this to work.\n\nThanks!\n",
